Telefonica May Buy Acens for 75 Million Euros, Economista Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-06-07T06:07:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-07/telefonica-may-buy-acens-for-75-million-euros-economista-says.html
Telefonica SA (TEF)  is close to buying
Acens, a Spanish company that specializes in cloud computing,
for about 75 million euros ($110 million), El Economista
reported, citing unidentified people close to the negotiations.  Acens is controlled by Nazca, a private-equity firm, and is
present in Madrid, Barcelona, Valencia and Bilbao; Telefonica
plans to use it to merge more than 100 data centers throughout
the world into six, of which two will be in Europe and two in
 Latin America , the newspaper said.  Telefonica may invest about 1.5 billion euros in total as
it integrates resources, El Economista said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
